<DocsLayout title="API" description="Silo API reference — REST endpoints and MCP tools.">
  <h1>API Reference</h1>

  <p>
    Silo exposes REST endpoints and MCP tools for AI agents, integrators, and developers.
  </p>

  <h2>REST API</h2>
  <p>
    The REST API provides endpoints for chat, judge profiling, graph operations, search,
    case workflow, and more. Authentication via API key. SSE streaming for chat.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="https://valter.sens.legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Full REST API documentation →</a>
  </p>

  <h2>MCP Tools</h2>
  <p>
    MCP tools enable AI agents (Claude, ChatGPT, and others) to search jurisprudence,
    analyze judge profiles, traverse the knowledge graph, and verify legal claims.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="https://valter.sens.legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Full MCP tools documentation →</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Auth:</strong> API key required for all endpoints</li>
    <li><strong>Rate limits:</strong> Enforced per key, fail-safe when Redis is unavailable</li>
    <li><strong>Streaming:</strong> SSE for chat endpoints</li>
    <li><strong>MCP remote:</strong> Available for Claude Desktop and ChatGPT Apps</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
